mes:  Irish Liam, Brendan, Brigid, Declan, Eoin, Seamus.","Irish (Antrim, especially Derry): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Catháin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Cathán</i>’, a personal name derived from <i>cath</i> ‘battle’. — Note: The population figure published by the US Census Bureau does not distinguish between the surnames <i>O'Kane</i> and   Okane  .","History: As lords of Keenaght in County Derry the O'Kanes were a leading sept in Ulster up to the time of the plantation (early 17th century)."]}]},{"name":"Okänt","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Liam, Brendan, Brigid, Declan, Eoin, Seamus.","Irish (Antrim, especially Derry): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Catháin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Cathán</i>’, a personal name derived from <i>cath</i> ‘battle’. — Note: The population figure published by the US Census Bureau does not distinguish between the surnames <i>O'Kane</i> and   Okane  .","History: As lords of Keenaght in County Derry the O'Kanes were a leading sept in Ulster up to the time of the plantation (early 17th century)."],"variants":[{"name":"Okane","meanings":["Anglicized form of the Irish Gaelic name Cathán, now also used elsewhere in the English-speaking world."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1357051,"age":24,"year":"1495","julianDay":2267098,"description":"Russians forces invade Sweden.","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1702078,"age":24,"year":"1495","toYear":"1497","julianDay":2267098,"title":"The Russo-Swedish War","description":"While in an alliance with Grand Prince Ivan III of Moscow, King Hans of Denmark and Norway invaded Sweden and was declared King of Sweden.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russo-Swedish_War_(1495%E2%80%931497)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Swedish War","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1702079,"age":49,"year":"1520","julianDay":2276228,"title":"The Stockholm Bloodbath","description":"A mass execution of Swedish nobles by Danish king Christian II is known as the Stockholm Bloodbath. Christian II invaded Sweden in 1519 and took hold of Stockholm in September 1520. Over 80 nobles were executed for heresy on November 8 and 9. The outrage from the executions led to the Swedish removal of support of the Kalmar Union.","url":"https://www.britannica.com/event/Stockholm-Bloodbath","urlTitle":"Britannica - Stockholm Bloodbath","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1702080,"age":52,"year":"1523","julianDay":2277324,"title":"Swedish War of Liberation","description":"The Swedish War of Liberation was a civil war led by nobleman Gustav Vasa. As Christian II heard of the rebellion, he confronted Vasa's men, who won the battle at Brunbacks Ferry. Christian II was defeated by the Swedes in Stockholm and a truce was agreed upon. Vasa was given as a hostage as a show of good faith until the treaty was signed. The Danish King did not keep his word and Vasa was held as a prisoner for two years until his escape. A bounty was placed on Vasa's head. Vasa worked to inspire many to join his cause and lived under disguise until the Danes surrendered in 1525.","url":"https://www.sweden.org.za/swedish-monarchy-gustav-vasa.html","urlTitle":"Sweden.org - Swedish Monarchy Gustav Vasa","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1702085,"age":69,"year":"1540","julianDay":2283533,"title":"First Full Swedish Translation of the Bible","description":"The first full Swedish translation of the Bible, known as the Gustav Bible, was completed by Olaus Petri and Laurentius Andreae and published in 1540.","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1702086,"age":73,"year":"1544","julianDay":2284994,"title":"Sweden Becomes Lutheran Nation","description":"Sweden officially declared itself a Lutheran nation in 1544.","jurisdictionLevel":3}],"lifeSummary":"Okänt Okänt was born in March 1470, in Innanbäcken, Nederkalix, Norrbotten, Sweden. She had at least 1 son with Jåp Jakob Jakobsson. She died in 1545, at the age of 75."},"et":{"1470 Innanbäcken 3, Framibyn, Nederkalix–1545":"